title: SpaceX to take over West Coast launch pad previously used by ULA
summary: SpaceX is getting a second launch pad on the West Coast after gaining approval to lease Space Launch Complex 6 (SLC-6) at Vandenberg Space Force Base, California, a historic pad previously occupied by United Launch Alliance.

title: Japanese ispace moon landing attempt falls short at ‘very end,’ CEO says

title: NASA Announces Student Winners of Power to Explore Challenge
